short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Google advanced search in natural language

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Make your Google search fields auto detect and perform advanced searches. Just write a natural language like advanced search and press (ctrl) + (enter) to perform if it was detected. It supports all possible advanced search properties and some other search settings such as dates, license type! Click on the "< >" icon, right of the search field if you want help on writing an advanced search. Click on the extension icon to read the usage guide. 

Examples
- news about barack obama from 2004-04-05 to 2006-05-05
- dog images for commercial use
- volvo v70 user manual filetype pdf
- recipes from japan in japanese

You can try it out before downloading at https://quantleaf.com.

Similar extension for Twitter: https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/twitter-natural-advanced/fkjippcbpjcnjfoohfhaghfelfanamee

Source code: https://github.com/quantleaf/google-natural-advanced-search

This extension was created using query.quantleaf.com, a service that lets you query tables with natural language.

Enjoy!
